        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(minimax): guard music generation SSE JSON.parse against malformed frames",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n**What problem does this PR solve?**\n\n- Fix classification: Crash-protection for malformed SSE data frames in MiniMax music generation.\n- Root cause: `readStreamingTrack:266` calls `JSON.parse(json)` on raw SSE `data:` frames without try/catch. The `try { ... } finally { ... }` block in the caller catches errors but a malformed frame throws unhandled `SyntaxError` instead of being gracefully skipped.\n- Why this is narrow fix: Wraps the single `JSON.parse` site, calls `continue` on failure — same skip path as empty/`[DONE]` frames. Note line 408 `JSON.parse` is already inside a `try {}` block.\n- Patch quality notes: 2 files, +34/-1 lines. v2 adds a regression test: malformed `data: NOT JSON {{{` frame skipped, valid terminal frame still produces an audio track.\n\n**Why does this matter now?**\n\n- User impact: Malformed SSE frame from MiniMax music streaming crashes the entire generation with raw SyntaxError.\n\n**What is intentionally out of scope?**\n\n- Does NOT change: valid SSE frame parsing, hex audio decoding, size-cap enforcement, or the already-protected line 408 JSON.parse.",
